<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-53-0992 </DOCNO><TEXT>Venezuela is one of the world's oldest and largest oil exporting countries.The oil industry has accumulative production to crude approaching 40billion barrels and close to 40,000 wells drilled to date. Proved reservesare 56 billion barrels, while total oil reserves recoverable under presenteconomic conditions are estimated at close to 200 billion barrels, includinga significant portion of those from the Orinoco Belt. This resource baseassures Venezuela's long-term role as an oil exporter.</TEXT></DOC>